I made small sale in the last two rounds to build a safety net for my family and a small pool to fund my own start-up.

We work really hard to make things happen and it feels great to be able to do something nice for the family as well in the journey.

When I was joining UC, my parents detested that I negotiated my fixed cash down in exchange of more ESOPs. 

Who does that? 

Will this remain paper money that may or may not realise? Will it take 5 years, 10 years, or never in my lifetime for this value to be become real?

People within the company realise this. They look at ESOPs as more valuable than the real money. 

Every year, during appraisals, I see a large number of people asking for their annual cash hike to be converted to ESOPs. 

I have done that myself, unsuccessfully though! :)

Result - 3 secondaries in 6 years since the company was founded. And, it is not about 10 oldest employees making 50 Cr each. It is about a large number of people levelling up in life. So many bought homes. So many paid off debt. So many became financially less stressed.

Strike price of Rs1, Infinite hold period that helps you manage liquidity, accelerated vesting, linear vesting - all of these are very sound and very rare (unfortunately) policies.

ESOPs are not an instrument of manipulation but instrument for sharing the value created.

I strongly believe that UC's ESOP program is probably one of the best and most employee centric across the WORLD. Value acceleration and value realisation is quite real. Very few companies have been able to demonstrate that pre-IPO.

People hate ESOPs. 

They look at it as bonus money. “Aaya to theek hai, nahi to koi baat nahi. Cash poora do”.

In fact, most precedents demonstrate that only very few employees end up sharing the upside in start-ups that are able to scale. https://t.co/O0EEmA6YL0
